#Edutic - Educode - education and technology in the classroom, Brussels, Belgium=

An international conference in the center of Brussels, Sunday 19 August - Wednesday 22 August 2018

During 4 days, in Bozar and the Royal Academy, teachers, school directors, parents and students, researchers are invited to reflect on the use of digital technology in teaching and teaching through digital all levels (primary, secondary and higher), with a part devoted to programming.

The event will be organized in 4 days for 4 audiences:

   1.     1 open days for the general public (Sunday 19 August and may be
   extended to Tuesday 21 August if there are strong expressions of interest)
   2.     2 days dedicated to teachers (Monday, August 20 and Tuesday, August 21)
   3.    1 day dedicated to school directors (Tuesday, August 21)
   4.     1 day devoted to scientific research on pedagogy, teaching and digital
   technologies (Wednesday 22 August)

##Contents

Some lectures but mainly practical workshops and presentations, especially by
teachers and their students, or by representatives of various specialized
companies or associations that contribute to the training in the use of ICT at
school (such as KodoWallonia, Devoxx4kids, SICarré, The hand in the dough, the
Scientothèque, the experimentarium, Molengeek, the actors of Fablab ...)

The steering team of the conference wishes to put at the service of the Pact of
Excellence its knowledge of the actors and its capacity of organization of
meetings between professionals of various horizons.

##Location
in Bozar and the Royal Academy (on the other side of Place Royale in Brussels)

##Activities

   *     Sun 19/8, 9h - 18h: schools, associations, companies are exhibiting
    their achievements and projects related to digital and education, and
    projects made in classrooms (in the corridors of Bozar and at the Academy)
   *     Sun 19/8 18h : Social get together dinner at the Academy

   *     Mon 20/8 7h - 9h : Registration, coffee & breakfast
   *     Mon 20/8 9h to 10h: Plenary conference of Thierry Karsenti, director of
   CRIFE in Montreal, *Panorama of the use of digital in class in Quebec and
   Canada*.
   *     Mon 20/8 from 10h to 17h: lectures and practical workshops
   (100 computers are installed in seminar rooms, and participants are
   invited to bring with their laptops)
   *     Mon 20/8 14h to 16h : Round Table Education and Technology in the
   World : *What works and what does not, and why, what could be done* (with
   national representatives from different countries, eg Argentine, Belgium,
   France, India, Québec etc)
   *     Mon 20/8 7:00 pm: Conference by Thomas Pesquet (ESA): *ESA's
   experiments with European students* (tbc)

   *     Tue 21/8 7h - 9h : Coffee & breakfast
   *     Tue 21/8 9h to 10h: Plenary Conference by Peter Hinssen (tbc)   *Understanding the revolutions around technology in 2018*
   *     Tue 21/8 from 10h to 17h: conferences and workshops specially dedicated
   to school directors are organized
   *     Tue 20/8 from 10h to 16h: lectures and practical workshops (continued)
   *     Tue 21/8 from 17h to 18h : closing plenary conference
   *     Tue 21/8 from 19h : Classical concert in the Henri LeBoeuf room
   *     Tue 21/8 22h : Farewell drink

   *     Wed 22/8 7h - 9h : Coffee & breakfast
   *     Wed 22/8 from 9h to 17h: a day devoted to research in education and digital
   *     Wed 22/8 18h - 22h : End of conference dinner

